# Cursor Rules — Kairo

Read `PROJECT.md` completely before suggesting or generating any code.
All conventions, stack decisions, and architecture boundaries are defined there.

## Cursor-specific preferences
- Always show diffs before applying multi-file changes
- Prefer explicit types over inference for function signatures
- When generating components, always include both ES and EN strings (see i18n rules in PROJECT.md)
- Never suggest `any` — suggest `unknown` with a type guard if truly uncertain
- For Hono routes, follow the existing pattern in `apps/api/src/routes/`
